My conceptual problems with this piece still stand. The long version of my complaints was lost when the prior version was deleted, but in brief:

The internal coverup is nonsensical and counterproductive. Intentional misinformation within the Foundation is expensive and dangerous for anything short of an infohazard, with rare exceptions like the Fountain of Youth; using it here is excessive and unjustified.
Setting aside the coverup, the only thing that this artifact does is pump out reality shifts (CK-class scenarios by my interpretation). Like any K-class scenario, CK events are only an interesting device when employed as a means to an end. A machine that triggers nonspecific XK events would make a boring SCP. This thing does nothing but trigger nonspecific CK events, to the same effect.


The writing is solid, the concept bugs the hell out of me. Downvote.







